{
  "stem": "21482.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we still didn't starve, and we still didn't freeze.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the last seven months of the war, when we were under Oskar Schindler's care and under Mrs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Emilie Schindler's care, well, we were protected.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Hundreds and hundreds, thousands of all the Jewish people, all my family, all my friends, they were sent on death marches [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] where they-- 90% of them died.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They froze to death.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They died of starvation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They died by the bullets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And young women, like my aunt-- my youngest aunt, my Aunt [INAUDIBLE], my mother's youngest sister-- was sent to a camp in Stutthof, which was on the Baltic Sea.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A few days before the war ended, the Germans put them in the lifeboats, set them free in the ocean, and machine gunned the lifeboats.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And 2,000 women drowned, just days before they would-- would have been liberated.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everything is documented.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans took such records.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They kept such-- everything in such detail.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that-- and then there were some survivors who did not go on that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They survived in the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything, really, that we know is because of the German records, because there are very few survivors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Germans themselves were so proud of what they were doing and felt they were doing such excellent job that they kept all the records.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To this day, you can find out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My cousin just found, recently, one-- one of my uncles, my father's brother, how he died in Flossenburg by a injection of gasoline two days before the war ended.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And so we on Schindler's List are so unbelievably lucky because, if it was not for Oskar Schindler, I would never be here.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I would never have survived.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
